ask Tracker App
A simple full-stack Task Tracker application built using React for the frontend and Node.js + Express for the backend. It allows users to add, view, and delete tasks in real time.

🚀 Features
📋 Add new tasks

✅ View all tasks

❌ Delete tasks

⚡ Fast and responsive UI with React

🔌 RESTful API powered by Express.js

🛠️ Tech Stack
Frontend:

React (Vite)

Axios

Backend:

Node.js

Express

CORS Middleware

📁 Folder Structure
bash
Copy
Edit
task-tracker/
├── client/       # React app
│   └── src/
│       └── App.jsx
├── server/       # Node.js backend
│   └── index.js
🧑‍💻 Getting Started
1. Clone the repository
bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/your-username/task-tracker.git
cd task-tracker
2. Start the backend server
bash
Copy
Edit
cd server
npm install
node index.js
3. Start the React frontend
bash
Copy
Edit
cd client
npm install
npm run dev
The app will run at http://localhost:5173 and connect to the backend on http://localhost:5000.

🌐 API Endpoints
Method	Endpoint	Description
GET	/api/tasks	Get all tasks
POST	/api/tasks	Add a new task
DELETE	/api/tasks/:id	Delete a task by ID

